explanation: Utilizes a HashMap to store element frequencies and two stacks: one for the main stack and another for tracking the minimum frequency elements. Pushing an element updates its frequency and ensures the minimum frequency stack reflects the current top element with the highest frequency. Popping retrieves the top element from the main stack, decrements its frequency, and maintains the integrity of the minimum frequency stack.

